  "theme": "Outlast the table's chaos with red tape — tax, audit, and recount everyone else's dice and coins while filing paperwork that quietly grinds the game to a halt.",
  "description": "Bureaucratrix Prim was never elected. She was simply always there — third desk from the window, beneath a sign that reads PLEASE TAKE A NUMBER. While the Mayor sets the table on fire, Prim files paperwork against the flames, and somehow the paperwork wins. This is the unelected deep state of Whateverville: an Azorius (WU) stax machine of permits, subpoenas, hold music, and Form 27-B that taxes, audits, and recounts everyone else's chaos until the game quietly grinds to a halt. Prim is gleefully parasitic — she profits whenever ANYONE at the table rolls a die, flips a coin, votes, recounts, or hands out a snack, and her audits let her reroll your luck and keep the result she prefers. An acorn (Un-set) Commander deck with chaos dialed deliberately LOW: most cards read like almost-functional Magic with a DMV-from-hell twist, thinning to a handful of chaos-5 fever-dreams — a form that fills itself out, a meeting that could have been an email. Color-identity and singleton rules are waived for acorn decks.",
